# Commit and docs hygiene

- Never use the em dash. Use a plain hyphen `-` instead.
- When writing commit messages, NEVER add an agent name as co-author (`Co-authored-by: Cursor` or similar).
- Never manually modify `CHANGELOG.md` or files marked auto-generated.
- When writing or substantially editing long Markdown, put each full sentence on its own line.
- After `git commit` / `git commit --amend`, verify there is no `Co-authored-by` trailer.
- If the tooling reinjects `Co-authored-by`, rebuild the commit with `git commit-tree` (see personal skill `git-commit-hygiene`) before pushing.
- GitHub Contributors includes historical co-authors. A clean Contributors list needs a new orphan history or a new repository, not only a tip-commit fix.
